2.0 Major Update (April 2025)\n\n### 🎯 Key Highlights:\n\n**💰 Dramatic Price Reduction**\n- **Old pricing:** $500/month\n- **New pricing:** $20/month starting price\n- Agent Compute Unit (ACU): $2.25 per unit\n\n### 🚀 New Features in Devin 2.0:\n\n1. **Parallel Devins & Cloud IDE**\n   - Launch multiple Devin instances simultaneously\n   - Interactive cloud-based IDE environment\n   - Handle multiple tasks concurrently\n   - Each Devin instance works independently\n\n2. **Enhanced Collaboration Modes**\n   - Users can closely monitor or take a hands-off approach\n   - Devin proactively involves users when needed\n   - Maintains user awareness and control throughout\n\n3. **Interactive Planning**\n   - Devin researches codebase and generates detailed initial plans\n   - Users can review and modify plans before execution\n   - Ensures AI understanding aligns with user goals\n\n4. **Direct Editing & Review**\n   - Review and modify code within Devin IDE\n   - Fine-tune or run tests directly\n   - Familiar keyboard shortcuts (Cmd+I, Cmd+K)\n\n### 📈 Performance Improvements:\n- **83% increase** in task completion efficiency per ACU\n- Beta users reported similar performance gains\n- VSCode-like interface for seamless interaction\n\n### 🔧 Previous Updates (Devin 1.2 - Early 2025):\n- Enhanced context reasoning\n- Voice command integration via Slack\n- Better code repository analysis\n- Enterprise features including machine snapshots\n- Usage-based billing model\n\n---\n\n**Note:** If you're looking for February 2026 updates specifically, you may need to check Cognition AI's official channels at a future date, as we're currently in early 2025. Would you like me to search for more recent information about Devin 2.0 or other Cognition AI developments?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
