新\",\"url\":\"https://zhidao.baidu.com/question/318127278511130644.html\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://apps.apple.com/mo/app/github/id1477376905\"}]\n\nBased on my web search, I found information about GitHub Copilot updates from February 2026. Here's a summary of the key updates and new features:\n\n## GitHub Copilot Updates - February 2026\n\n### Major Model Update\n- **GPT‑5.3‑Codex Integration** (Released February 9, 2026)\n  - New model generally available across GitHub Copilot experiences\n  - 25% improvement in agentic development task speed\n  - Available in Visual Studio Code, GitHub.com, GitHub Mobile (iOS/Android), GitHub CLI, and Copilot Coding Agent\n  - Enterprise/Business administrators need to explicitly enable this model in settings\n\n### Model Deprecations (February 17, 2026)\nGitHub deprecated several Anthropic and OpenAI models across all Copilot experiences, including:\n- Copilot Chat\n- Inline edits\n- Ask mode\n- Agent modes\n- Code completions\n\n### GitHub Global Developer Conference Updates\nDuring a global developer conference in February 2026, GitHub announced:\n\n**Copilot Enhancements:**\n- Support for more editors (Neovim and JetBrains IDEs like IntelliJ IDEA and PyCharm)\n- Multi-line code completion support for Java, C, C++, and C#\n- Support for additional programming languages beyond Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, Ruby, and Go\n\n**Broader Platform Updates:**\n- 20,000+ product improvements across GitHub\n- New GitHub Issue beta with iteration support and custom fields\n- GitHub Discussions upgrades with Actions integration\n- Codespaces cloud development environment updates\n\n### Other Notable Features\n- GitHub Mobile app improvements for Copilot agent tasks\n- Better pull request review experience\n- Zed editor support for Copilot subscriptions\n\n**Note:** Some specific details about individual features may vary by region and subscription tier (Pro, Pro+, Business, Enterprise). The GPT‑5.3‑Codex model requires explicit administrative enablement for organizational accounts.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
