y limitation: small context window makes it struggle with project-wide understanding\n\n### **Windsurf (formerly Codeium)**\n\n- **Remote indexing** - puts codebase indexing in the cloud, supporting projects with 1M+ lines of code\n- **Cascade Agentic assistant** - deep context awareness, multi-file editing, direct file writing\n- **Cross-IDE support** - not just VS Code, but entire JetBrains family (IntelliJ, WebStorm, PyCharm, etc.)\n- Pricing:\n  - Personal: **Free**\n  - Pro: $15/month\n- Key differentiator: minimal local resource usage for massive repositories\n\n### **Market Context**\n\nAccording to a comprehensive comparison from February 2026:\n- **85% of developers** are using AI coding tools\n- **41% of code** is generated by AI\n- Only **3% of developers** say they \"highly trust\" AI-written code\n- The market has shifted from simple autocomplete to **multi-agent systems** and **project-aware coding**\n\n### **Recommended Combinations (Total $46/month)**\n\nThe optimal setup suggested for different scenarios:\n1. **Copilot Pro ($10)** - for everyday completions and quick tasks\n2. **Cursor Pro ($16)** - for full-time coding with multi-file editing\n3. **Claude Code Pro ($20)** - for architecture-level operations and complex refactoring\n\nEach tool serves a different purpose: Copilot for speed, Cursor for project awareness, and Claude Code for deep architectural work and large-scale refactoring."
